				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${{{{\rm{Grp}}}}}_{{{{{\rm{PoS}}}}}_{1},{{{{\rm{PoS}}}}}_{2}}$$\end{document} (i.e. whether the group is found at either or both of the two positions). Finally, the intensity of the differently coloured edges around the nodes represents the importance of typical, common, or uncommon groups of chemical residues for a specific position (blue, green and red, respectively). A list of the actual importance values can be found in Supplementary Table 2 in the ESI, and a more detailed explanation of the features is given in the ‘Methods’ section.

